title: Jake Sullivan’s ‘Quieter’ Middle East Comments Did Not Age Well
description: The national security adviser has drawn criticism for recent public remarks. Biden officials pushed back on the idea that Mr. Sullivan was offering a lasting view on Middle East conflicts.

title: Hamas Leaders Arrive in Russia as the Kremlin Attempts to Showcase Clout
description: The meetings with high-ranking members of the group that attacked Israel underscored how Russia is trying to present itself as an alternative platform for possible mediation.

title: Israeli Tanks Raid Gaza Ahead of Invasion, While Aid Trickles In
description: The United States has advised delaying a ground invasion, in part to get more desperately needed aid, which has flowed slowly, into Gaza.

title: Disagreements Among Israeli Leaders Delay Gaza Ground Invasion
description: In the 20 days since Hamas attacked, Israel’s Air Force has pounded Gaza and its troops have gotten into position. But its leaders disagree about what to do next.

title: Friday Briefing: Israel Says Tanks Briefly Entered Gaza
description: Plus inspiration in the Rugby World Cup final.

title: What to Know About UNRWA, the Largest Aid Organization in Gaza
description: Established to provide temporary relief for Palestinians who fled or were expelled from their homes during the 1948 Arab-Israeli war, the agency now mainly provides services and funding for those registered as Palestinian refugees across the Mideast.

title: Slovakia to Halt Arms Deliveries to Ukraine, as New Leader Promised
description: The newly appointed prime minister, Robert Fico, whose party aligned with pro-Russian forces during the recent election campaign, had promised “not to send a single cartridge” of ammunition to Kyiv.

title: Air Canada Apologizes for Questioning a British Lawmaker About His Background
description: The airline and Canadian immigration officials were accused of singling out the lawmaker, Mohammad Yasin, “because his name was Mohammad.”

title: Israel-Hamas War Looms Over Saudi Arabia Forum
description: The kingdom is embracing business as usual, hosting an investment forum, concerts and even fashion shows. But grief, fear and outrage over Israel’s bombardment of Gaza simmer just below the surface.

title: As Violence Surges, Nations Seek U.S. Defense Pacts. Some Americans Are Wary.
description: Many countries, including Ukraine and Israel, want greater U.S. protection against Russia, China, Iran and North Korea. But some Americans resist further military commitments.

title: As Violence Surges, Nations Seek U.S. Defense Pacts. Some Americans Are Wary.
description: Many countries want greater U.S. protection against Russia, China, Iran and North Korea. But some American lawmakers and voters resist further military commitments.

title: Who Is in Israel’s War Cabinet?
description: Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu said that the small group of officials would play a key role in determining when Israel begins a ground invasion of Gaza.

title: As Winter Nears, Ukraine Braces for Attacks on Energy Grid
description: Russia targeted power systems last year and recent attacks suggest a return to that strategy, raising anxiety among Ukrainian civilians and officials.

title: Dave Chappelle Laments ‘Nightmare’ Facing Israelis and Palestinians
description: The comedian, whose remarks about the Israel-Hamas war last week made headlines, returned to the subject at a show in North Carolina.

title: Israel-Hamas War: Israeli Tanks Briefly Enter Gaza After Netanyahu Vows Hamas Will ‘Pay the Price’
description: The Israeli military said the tank raid was in preparation for the “next stages of combat.” Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu indicated that a ground invasion was likely, but did not give specifics.

title: After Hurricane Otis, Mexican Officials Survey the Damage
description: The storm was one of the strongest ever to hit the southwest coast, but the extent of the destruction in Acapulco and elsewhere was unclear early Thursday.

title: Local Police in Ofakim Defended the Israeli City From Hamas’s Attacks
description: Military support was slow to arrive in the quiet desert city of Ofakim but officers, most of them armed with handguns, fought terrorists house to house.

title: South Korea Must Return Buddhist Statue to Japan, Supreme Court Says
description: The artifact, which was taken to Tsushima centuries ago, was stolen and smuggled back to South Korea by thieves in 2012.

title: Thursday Briefing
description: Biden calls for more aid into Gaza.

title: In Demark, Eviction and Demolition Remake ‘Non-Western’ Neighborhoods
description: A government program is using demolition and relocation to remake neighborhoods with “non-Western” immigrants, poverty or crime.

title: Several Family Members of Al Jazeera’s Gaza Bureau Chief Are Killed
description: Wael al-Dahdouh, described by his colleagues as “the voice of Palestinians in Gaza,” lost his wife, son, daughter and infant grandson, Al Jazeera said.
